@TOC "MAIN"

                               Introduction

Bull Quiz was original made way back in 1996 when Bulldog Productions first
started to program programs and games for CNet BBS Software.

THe game started off very basic at first, and was intened to be a clone of
a game Daniel Garnett, played on a BBS in Manchester, Run on a PC. Sadly
this bbs has since been closed.

This version of Bull Quiz, version 3.0 has been greatly improved, it now
has better graphics, faster loading options, Fully registered and the
questions (Produced by Mark Davies) have been either updated or fixed.

For more information of forth comming Bulldog Productions programs for CNet
or any other software by Bulldog Productions Please call @{"Bad Obsession BBS" LINK "Technical Support"}.

**************************************************************************
******* Bulldog Productions - Bull Quiz Version 3.0 - 29-May-1997 ********
**************************************************************************
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirments" "Bull Quiz 3 Requirments"
@NEXT "Installation"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "MAIN"

                                Requirments

Bull Quiz 3 was written on an Amiga 1200 Running at 33mhz With 6meg Memory.
This game does use RAM: quite a lot so the chances are you will not be able
to run it on a small memory based machine. I know for a fact that it
doesn't run on a CNet BBS On a standard Amiga 1200.. If you do have any
problems or need any information or help please contact me on @{"Bad Obsession" LINK "Technical Support"}
BBS.

**************************************************************************
******* Bulldog Productions - Bull Quiz Version 3.0 - 29-May-1997 ********
**************************************************************************
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Bull Quiz 3 Installation"
@NEXT "Technical Support"
@PREV "Requirments"
@TOC "MAIN"

                               Installation

Bull Quiz is very easy to install theres no complicated setups or variables
you have to alter.. All you need to do is copy all files into your PFILES
drawer in another drawer called BULLQUIZ3 and thats it.. You may have
already done this by just Un-LHAing straight into Pfiles.. :)

Once all files have been moved log on to your BBS and where-ever you want
to stick it Add it as an Arexx File, the only flagged needed to be changed
is make sure that only ONE player can play it at once..

If you want to install it so it can be played anywhere on the bbs load up
your BBSMENU text file and at the bottom of option 2; Available Everywhere,
add the line

QUIZ `1- | {#0pfiles:bullquiz3/bullquiz3.rexx}

Please remember the { is a CTRL+Q :)

**************************************************************************
******* Bulldog Productions - Bull Quiz Version 3.0 - 29-May-1997 ********
**************************************************************************
